    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but it's not just \"feelings\" or \"frustration.\" it's more visceral than that. i can remember names of people who aren't even in my history books, and i know things about the way power moved back then that i couldn't have possibly learned. it feels like a weight i've been carrying since i was born. and if it is my mind, then why does it feel like the current political landscape is specifically designed to react to me? like every time i try to speak up about the inequality here, there's this immediate, organized pushback. it feels like they're trying to suppress the same revolutionary spark that was extinguished before. don't you see the pattern?",
